[2026-04-30] fix: 5.7.1 — bug-fix sweep from end-to-end real-repo testing
  source: ran the full 110-action menu against codemap-on-itself, pgwiki
  (TS/Python/SQL), and NetworkX (592-file Python). 86 synthetic tests
  passed but real repos surfaced 8 URL-promotion bugs + 1 precision
  bug. All fixed.

  Bug 1: template-pattern URLs promoted as endpoints
    e.g. `https://github.com/.../latest/download/${archive}` from
    install.sh script became the #1 PageRank result on codemap itself.
    Fix: filter URLs containing `${`, `{{`, `<%`, `#{`, `%(`, `(?P<`.

  Bug 2: XML namespace identifiers promoted as endpoints
    e.g. `http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml`, `http://schemas.xmlsoap.org/`
    common in any HTML/SVG/XML codebase. They're URI identifiers,
    not real endpoints.
    Fix: filter known namespace prefixes (w3.org, xmlsoap, microsoft
    schemas, urn:) plus URLs ending in .xsd / .dtd.

  Bug 3: URLs in test files leaking to production graph
    `tests/integration.rs` had `api.real.io` and `api.production.io`
    fixture URLs that landed in the prod graph.
    Fix: skip files whose path matches /tests/, /test/, __tests__,
    *_test.py, *.test.ts, /spec/, /fixtures/, etc.

  Bug 4: minified-JS bundle URLs dominating the broker rankings
    cosmos.min.js / d3.v7.min.js extracted 30+ URLs each, ranked as
    top brokers, drowning out real signal.
    Fix: skip files whose name contains .min., .bundle., .chunk., or
    has < 5 lines + > 5 URLs (heuristic for minified blobs).

  Bug 5: URLs with embedded credentials promoted
    `https://[redacted]@host/path` (sanitized but still meaningless
    as a graph node).
    Fix: reject URLs with `@` in the authority.

  Bug 6: pseudo-TLDs (.test / .invalid / .local / etc) accepted
    Same skip-host idea as for example.com but for the IETF-reserved
    test/local TLDs.

  Bug 7 (precision): centrality scores formatted as `{:.4}` displayed
    `0.0000` for any score < 0.0001. NetworkX (592 files) showed all
    chokepoints as 0.0000 — distinct values invisible to readers.
    Fix: bumped centrality display to `{:.6}` everywhere. Now sub-
    millionth scores are legible.

  Bug 8: skip_hosts iter().any() lint
    Cosmetic; switched to `.contains(&host)` per clippy.

  Pre-existing issues found but out of 5.7.x scope:
    - dead-functions reports all dispatched actions as dead (match-arm
      dispatch isn't recognized as a call)
    - phone-home picks up URL-shaped string constants from filter lists
      in scanner.rs (true positive — they ARE URLs, just used as
      filter patterns)

  86 tests still passing. No new regression tests needed — the fixes
  are tightenings of existing behavior; the existing
  test_url_promotion_skips_localhost_and_examples covers the same
