[2026-04-30] fix: 5.7.3 — dead-functions match-arm dispatch + ELF/Mach-O Dll deps + UX
  source: closing the remaining bug list from the 5.7.x sweep.

  Fix 1: dead-functions reported all dispatched actions as dead
    On codemap-on-itself it flagged 141 false positives (every action
    that's reachable through `match action { "stats" => stats(g) }`).
    Root cause: parser captures call expression `analysis::stats` as
    qualified path, but dead-fn check looks up bare name `stats`.
    Fix: index call sites by BOTH the qualified path AND the trailing
    segment after `::` or `.`. Now matches both Rust (`mod::fn`) and
    Python (`mod.fn`) dispatch patterns.
    Result: 141 false positives → 17 real candidates.

  Fix 2: ELF binaries don't expose library deps
    pe-imports registers PeBinary → Dll → Symbol nodes; elf-info only
    classified the binary itself even though parse_elf was already
    extracting DT_NEEDED entries internally.
    Fix: refactored parse_elf → parse_elf_with_deps returning (info,
    Vec<String>). elf_info now registers each NEEDED library as a Dll
    node with edges from the binary, mirroring the PE pattern. After
    `codemap elf-info /usr/bin/grep`, `pagerank dll` surfaces libc.so.6
    + libpcre2-8.so.0 + ld-linux-aarch64.so.1; `meta-path elf->dll`
    finds 3 paths.

  Fix 3: Mach-O binaries don't expose dylib deps
    Same gap — parse_macho_detail captured LC_LOAD_DYLIB / LC_LOAD_
    WEAK_DYLIB / LC_REEXPORT_DYLIB internally but didn't surface them.
    Fix: added lightweight `extract_macho_dylibs` helper that re-walks
    the load commands and returns just the dylib names (handles single-
    arch + fat binaries). macho_info registers them as Dll nodes.

  Fix 4: empty-target UX on coupling/exports
    `coupling ""` produced "0 files coupled to ''" (matched everything
    via .contains("")); `exports ""` produced an "ambiguous match for
    \"\"" warning across the entire graph.
    Fix: coupling now shows usage hint; exports lists top 30 files
    by export count when target is empty.

  Tests: 91 passing (was 87). +4 new regression tests covering
  ELF DT_NEEDED → Dll edges, dead-functions module-dispatch
  recognition, coupling empty-target usage, exports empty-target
  list-all behavior.

[2026-04-30] feat: 5.8.0 — algorithms expansion (110 → 131 actions)
  source: Charles asked "does our tool miss anything else those guys
  have?" Honest gap analysis vs Joern / NetworkX / petgraph identified
  21 missing actions worth adding. All shipped this release.

  Centrality: NetworkX 11/17 → 17/17 (full coverage)
    - subgraph-centrality (Estrada-Rodriguez 2005, exp(A) diagonal)
    - second-order (Kermarrec 2011, return-time variance)
    - dispersion (Lou-Strogatz local dispersion)
    - reaching (asymmetric forward-reach)
    - trophic (food-web hierarchy levels — 1=entry, ↑=deep)
    - current-flow-closeness (Brandes-Fleischer random-walk closeness)

  Classical algorithms (petgraph parity — actions/algorithms.rs):
    - bellman-ford <src> — single-source shortest paths
    - astar <src> <tgt> — A* with binary heap
    - floyd-warshall — all-pairs shortest paths (refuses on n>2000)
    - diameter — graph diameter via BFS-from-each-node
    - mst — minimum spanning tree (Kruskal + union-find)
    - cliques — maximum cliques (Bron-Kerbosch with pivoting)
    - kshortest <src> <tgt> [k] — Yen's k-shortest paths (default k=5)
    - max-flow <src> <sink> — Edmonds-Karp BFS Ford-Fulkerson
    - feedback-arc — DFS-based feedback arc set heuristic

  Link prediction (actions/link_prediction.rs):
    - common-neighbors — |N(u) ∩ N(v)| for unconnected pairs
    - jaccard — |shared| / |union|, normalized for degree
    - adamic-adar — Σ 1/log(degree(shared neighbor))
    Surface missing-import bugs and "files that should know each
    other but don't."

  Community detection (actions/community.rs, beyond Leiden + LPA):
    - k-core [k] — peel by degree threshold (find dense skeleton)
    - k-clique [k] — Palla et al. 2005 k-clique percolation
    - modularity-max — Clauset-Newman-Moore greedy modularity
    - divisive — Girvan-Newman edge-betweenness (refuses on n>500)

  Total LOC: ~1900 across 3 new modules (algorithms.rs ~600,
  link_prediction.rs ~140, community.rs ~400) + centrality.rs
