[2026-04-30] feat: 5.9.0 — Tier 1 algorithm completeness (+ graph export formats)
  source: post-5.8.0 gap analysis identified 6 algorithms still
  missing for petgraph/NetworkX/CodeQL parity. All shipped.

  Algorithms (extend actions/algorithms.rs):
    - scc — Tarjan's strongly-connected components, iterative form to
      avoid stack overflow on deep graphs. Reports cyclic-dependency
      clusters by size.
    - topo-sort — Kahn's algorithm, errors with helpful pointer to
      `scc` if graph isn't acyclic.
    - dominator-tree — Cooper-Harvey-Kennedy iterative dominator,
      auto-detects entry node (no-incoming-edges max-fanout) or
      takes target.
    - steiner — minimum-edge subgraph connecting N terminal nodes,
      MST heuristic (2-approximation).
    - subgraph-iso — VF2-style isomorphism for kind-sequence patterns,
      capped at 100 matches.

