[2026-04-30] feat: 5.12.0 — symbol demangling + language fingerprinting + Compiler nodes
  source: post-5.11 RE gap-analysis. pe-exports / elf-info / pe-imports
  were printing raw mangled names like _ZN5tokio4time5sleep17h... and
  ?MyFunc@Foo@@QAEHXZ — useless for human reading. Plus no way to
  triage "is this a Rust binary or a Go binary or .NET" without manual
  string-grepping.

  Two new modules + 1 new action:
    - src/demangle.rs (~330 LOC) — Itanium C++ ABI, MSVC C++, Rust
      legacy (_ZN..17h<hash>E), Rust v0 (_R...). Pure pattern-match,
      no external dep. Wired into pe-exports + pe-imports + elf-info
      output; demangled name becomes the canonical Symbol id; raw
      mangled goes to attrs["mangled"]. macOS double-underscore
      prefix (`__Z...`) handled.
    - src/fingerprint.rs (~250 LOC) — section-name + signature-string
      heuristics for Go (.gopclntab / runtime.morestack), Rust
      (__rust_alloc / RUST_BACKTRACE / rust_eh_personality), .NET
      (BSJB metadata / mscorlib), PyInstaller (_MEIPASS), Nuitka,
      Electron (V8 + node_modules), Delphi (Borland / @System@),
      MinGW vs MSVC vs GCC (CRT signatures), Swift (libswiftCore),
      C-extensions (Py_InitModule). Returns (language, compiler,
      runtime, confidence).
    - actions/lang_fp.rs (~250 LOC) — `codemap lang-fingerprint
      <binary>` action. Reads file, sniffs format from magic bytes,
      runs heuristics, registers Compiler node + binary→compiler
      edge with attrs. Idempotent.

  New EntityKind: Compiler (kind: "compiler"). Lets meta-path
  queries answer "every Go-compiled binary in this repo" or
  "what toolchains do we ship?"

  Scan window for fingerprinting: 64 MB cap (was 1 MB in initial
  draft — Rust signatures often live in .rodata which sits ~5 MB
  into a stripped release binary, so 1 MB missed them). NOT run
  during default scan; only on explicit invocation.

  Live verification:
    - codemap on itself (Rust binary, 26 MB) → detected as
      lang=rust compiler=rustc, confidence 90/100.
    - libstdc++.so.6 on Ubuntu (1900+ symbols) → demangling reveals
      `__gnu_cxx::stdio_sync_filebuf<...>::pbackfail` and similar
      readable forms; raw mangled retained as attrs["mangled"].

  Tests: 130 passing (was 114). +16 unit tests covering 9 demangle
  cases (Itanium simple/nested/macOS-prefix, Rust legacy with hash
  strip, Rust v0 crate root, MSVC simple/nested, unmangled
  passthrough, namespace splitting) + 7 fingerprint cases.

  Action count: 145 → 146 (+1).

